7 An Act relating to motor vehicles; prohibiting
certain entities from providing certain
8 recommendations; providing certain cause of civil
action for certain violation; prohibiting certain
9 entities from withholding certain grants in certain
circumstance; providing certain cause of civil action
10 for certain violation; providing for codification;
providing an effective date; and declaring an
11 emergency.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 808.1 of Title 47, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. 1. No agency, entity, or instrumentality of this state, or
19 entity contracted with such, shall provide specific recommendations
20 in favor of or against a commercial driver training school in this
21 state.
22 2. A violation of the provisions of paragraph 1 of this
23 subsection shall be a cause of civil action for the commercial
24 driver training school affected by such violation against the
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1595 Page 1

1 viol ating agency, entity, or instrumentality, or entity contracted
2 with such.
3 B. 1. No agency, entity, or instrumentality of this state, or
4 entity contracted with such, that administers grants for students of
5 commercial driver training schools in this state shall withhold such
6 grants based on the student’s choice of a specific school.
7 2. A violation of the provisions of paragraph 1 of this
8 subsection shall be a cause of civil action for the commercial
9 driver training school or student affected by such violation against
10 the violating agency, entity, or instrumentality, or entity
11 contracted with such.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
13 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
14 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
15 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
16 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
